description: out- +‎ lie (in the sense of "tell an untruth").

verbs.description: outlie (third-person singular simple present outlies, present participle outlying, simple past and past participle outlied)

entries.meaning: (rare, transitive) To tell more or better lies than.

description: out- +‎ lie (in the sense of "be located").

verbs.description: outlie (third-person singular simple present outlies, present participle outlying, simple past outlay, past participle outlain)
